        mButtonStartPause.setText(&quot;pause&quot;);
        mButtonReset.setVisibility(View.INVISIBLE);
    }

When you touch the mButtonStartPause button to start the timer in the first time, your code should call the startTimer() function.
To do that you check the value of mTimerRunning, **but there is no any value there**. The value will be set only in startTimer().

You need to give a value to the mTimerRunning variable before you try to use it.
The error happened because you tried to use something that doesn&#39;t exist.

Fix it by giving a value (false) to mTimerRunning right when you declare it:

